The paper deals with complexity classes and problems related to graph theory, combinatorics, algebra, and number theory, which are all topics covered by the above sub-categories. Specifically, the paper discusses the PPA complexity class, which is a class of NP-search problems reducible to the parity principle in undirected graphs, making cs.CC and cs.DS the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions problems related to the Combinatorial Nullstellensatz and the Chevalley-Warning Theorem, which are topics in algebraic geometry and algebraic combinatorics, respectively, making cs.CG, cs.DM, and cs.GT likely sub-categories as well.
